1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.466
Knox cloud services 26.06 release highlights.

2
00:00:03.466 --> 00:00:07.036
Here are the new features in the Knox Manage original console.

3
00:00:07.036 --> 00:00:10.611
Administer directory resources with Google Workspace.

4
00:00:10.612 --> 00:00:13.969
Starting with this release, you can now sync directory resources 

5
00:00:13.969 --> 00:00:16.117
directly from your Google Admin Console.

6
00:00:16.118 --> 00:00:18.782
This integration lets you synchronize resources 

7
00:00:18.782 --> 00:00:21.446
like users and groups to your Knox Manage tenant,

8
00:00:21.447 --> 00:00:25.654
allowing your device users to sign in with their existing Google accounts.

9
00:00:25.654 --> 00:00:29.632
To set up this connection, go to Settings, Android, 

10
00:00:29.966 --> 00:00:31.132
Google Workspace,

11
00:00:31.566 --> 00:00:33.132
then click "Sign in with Google"

12
00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:36.933
to link your Google Admin Console with your Managed Google Domain account.

13
00:00:37.633 --> 00:00:39.864
Support for Bulk eSIM Management.

14
00:00:39.864 --> 00:00:43.899
The original console introduces the ability to manage eSIMs in bulk, 

15
00:00:43.899 --> 00:00:48.965
which offers IT admins centralized control over eSIM provisioning across their device fleet.

16
00:00:49.266 --> 00:00:51.444
On the Bulk eSIM Management page,

17
00:00:51.445 --> 00:00:54.355
simply upload a spreadsheet containing eSIM activation 

18
00:00:54.356 --> 00:00:57.133
codes paired with their corresponding device IMEIs.

19
00:00:57.366 --> 00:01:01.732
Once uploaded, each activation code IMEI pair appears in the list with its current eSIM status.

20
00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.659
If your device's status is set to Enrolled,

21
00:01:04.659 --> 00:01:07.553
you can provision its eSIM by selecting it from the list, 

22
00:01:07.553 --> 00:01:09.499
then clicking Activate eSIM.

23
00:01:10.066 --> 00:01:14.232
Note that this feature requires devices running Android 15 or later.

24
00:01:14.466 --> 00:01:17.069
To use this feature with wearable devices, 

25
00:01:17.070 --> 00:01:19.966
they must be running Wear OS 16 or later.

26
00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.300
Auto-collect EID Numbers.

27
00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:27.038
With this release, the original console can automatically collects 

28
00:01:27.038 --> 00:01:31.566
EID numbers from your enrolled devices, which you can view from three different places:

29
00:01:31.566 --> 00:01:34.999
either by opening the device details panel and clicking the Network tab,

30
00:01:38.200 --> 00:01:41.166
Adding EID as a column on the Device page table, 

31
00:01:43.733 --> 00:01:45.933
or exporting your device list to Excel.

32
00:01:48.966 --> 00:01:50.966
To learn more about the features in this release, 

33
00:01:50.966 --> 00:01:52.899
or to get additional support at any time, 

34
00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:55.933
see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com.

35
00:01:56.166 --> 00:01:57.266
Thanks for watching!

